<div type="translation">
<head>Translation</head>
<p>[?The council and the people honoured ?Julius] Aureli[us Charidemos the] sophist [ priest for life of the God Dio]nysos [...] [descendant of high]priests [and ... -s and those who shared in the found]ing of the [city, having] carried out [?the greatest ] magistracies and lit[urgies hon]ourably [and having ? improved] many [ things ?for the city] [...] money [....]</p>
</div>
<div type="commentary">
<head>Commentary</head>
<p>As Robert pointed out, the man honoured may be Julius Aurelius Charidemos Iulianos, known from <xref type="inscription" n="1585" href="120909">12.909</xref>, or his father Claudius Aurelius Zelos, with a further epithet; both men were sophists.</p>
</div>
